## Organization Account: Enabled

We have decided to **create an Organization Account** for centralized management of our Snowflake environment.

**Capabilities That Will Be Enabled:**

| Capability | Description |
|------------|-------------|
| Centralized View | Single pane of glass for all accounts in the organization |
| Unified Billing | Consolidated cost management and billing across accounts |
| Account Provisioning | Ability to create and manage child accounts programmatically |
| Organization Policies | Apply governance policies across all accounts |
| Cross-Account Features | Enable data sharing, replication, and failover between accounts |
| ORGADMIN Role | Manage organization-level objects and users across accounts |

**Requirements:**
- ✅ Snowflake Enterprise Edition or higher
- ✅ ORGADMIN role granted in the existing account

**Important Notes:**
- The Organization Account should **not** contain business data
- It is used exclusively for administrative and management purposes
- Additional ACCOUNTADMIN users should be added for redundancy

**Next Step:** In the next step, you will create the actual Organization Account, including the account name, administrator details, edition, and region.

{%- else %}

## Organization Account: Not Enabled

We have decided **not to create an Organization Account** at this time.

**Implications:**
- Single-account deployment without centralized management features
- Organization-level features are not available
- Can be enabled later if you select or upgrade to Snowflake edition Enterprise or higher

**Next Step:** You will skip the Create Organization Account step and continue to the next configuration step.

{%- endif %}

## Key Terminology

| Term | Definition |
|------|------------|
| Organization | A Snowflake object that links accounts owned by your business entity |
| Organization Name | Your Snowflake business entity identifier (e.g., `ACME` or `XY12345`) |
| Organization Account | A special account type with ORGADMIN privileges for managing other accounts |
| Organization Account Name | The name you assign to your Organization Account (configured in the next step if enabled) |